1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:02,761
Start with the decision, not the topic.

2
00:00:02,711 --> 00:00:05,884
Research the home-care market” names a subject.

3
00:00:05,884 --> 00:00:13,240
Decide which customer segment our regional service should enter next year” gives the research a user, a consequence, and a finish line.

4
00:00:13,240 --> 00:00:15,211
Name the audience as well.

5
00:00:15,211 --> 00:00:22,961
A founder choosing a market needs different evidence from a product manager prioritizing features or a policy team assessing regulatory exposure.

6
00:00:22,961 --> 00:00:28,346
The same facts can be organized differently because the decision and the accountable reader are different.

7
00:00:28,346 --> 00:00:31,721
Then name the deliverable that would make the decision possible.

8
00:00:31,721 --> 00:00:41,653
It might be a one-page executive brief, a competitor comparison, a recommendation memo, an annotated bibliography, or a table of market signals with dates and confidence.

9
00:00:41,653 --> 00:00:44,817
A deliverable gives the research a visible end state.

10
00:00:44,817 --> 00:00:49,230
Choose Search or Deep Research based on the work, not the prestige of the tool.

11
00:00:49,230 --> 00:00:52,846
Search is enough for fast orientation and current updates.

12
00:00:52,846 --> 00:01:01,855
Deep Research earns its cost when the question needs multiple steps, conflicting sources, several sub-questions, or a structured synthesis that others must audit.

13
00:01:01,855 --> 00:01:07,548
For example, “What happened in grocery delivery during the last ninety days?” may begin with Search.

14
00:01:07,548 --> 00:01:16,115
How is private-label adoption changing competitive exposure, and what should a branded manufacturer do?” needs multiple evidence threads and a decision-ready brief.

15
00:01:16,115 --> 00:01:20,442
The common failure is upgrading every fuzzy question into Deep Research.

16
00:01:20,442 --> 00:01:23,269
More depth cannot repair a missing decision.

17
00:01:23,269 --> 00:01:27,942
It only produces a larger pile of information whose relevance no one has defined.

18
00:01:27,942 --> 00:01:32,201
First, connect the research to one accountable decision and audience.

19
00:01:32,201 --> 00:01:36,230
Second, define the deliverable that would make that decision possible.

20
00:01:36,230 --> 00:01:41,079
Third, choose research depth from the number of steps and evidence threads required.
